lead_paragraph: Phil Mickelson lamented his poor course management after compiling his worst ever score at Augusta National, a seven-over 79, to miss the cut after the second round at the Masters on Friday.

headline.print_headline: Three Double Bogeys Cost Mickelson Cut at Masters
